question: What are the survival chances of allgery Shellfish (substance)?
answers:
SELECT p.RACE, p.ETHNICITY, p.GENDER, p.BIRTHDATE, p.DEATHDATE, 
                    COUNT(*) AS TOTAL_ALLERGY, 
                    SUM(CASE WHEN a.CODE = 'Shellfish' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS SHELLFISH_ALLERGY
             FROM patients p
             LEFT JOIN allergies a ON p.Id = a.PATIENT
             WHERE a.CODE IS NOT NULL
             GROUP BY p.RACE, p.ETHNICITY, p.GENDER, p.BIRTHDATE, p.DEATHDATE
             ORDER BY TOTAL_ALLERGY DESC;

question: What is the successrate of medication Simvastatin 10 MG Oral Tablet?
answers:
SELECT 
                COUNT(DISTINCT p.Id) AS Total_Patients,
                COUNT(DISTINCT m.Id) AS Total_Medications,
                COUNT(DISTINCT m.Id) / COUNT(DISTINCT p.Id) AS Success_Rate
            FROM 
                patients p
                JOIN encounters e ON p.Id = e.PATIENT
                JOIN medications m ON e.Id = m.ENCOUNTER
            WHERE 
                m.CODE = 'Simvastatin 10 MG Oral Tablet' AND 
                m.PAYER = (SELECT Id FROM payers WHERE NAME = 'Medicare') AND 
                e.START >= DATE_TRUNC('month', CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '1 year') AND 
                e.START <= DATE_TRUNC('month', CURRENT_DATE)
            GROUP BY 
                p.Id
            HAVING 
                COUNT(DISTINCT m.Id) / COUNT(DISTINCT p.Id) > 0.5;
